Police are looking for a taxi driver who took off with his passenger&#39;s belongings at Jomo Kenyatta International Airport on Tuesday. The driver who had picked the woman up in the city centre drove off after dropping her at the screening point. The Kenyan passenger told police she was headed for Juba, South Sudan. &nbsp;After being screened, the driver sped off with her three bags, which had her academic certificates and a laptop among other things. She cited the registration number of the suspect&#39;s&nbsp;car as KBY 613G. ALSO READ: Police probe theft of 22 digital literacy tablets in Trans Nzoia